<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 76-year-old La Jolla man was killed and his wife received minor injuries when 
he attempted to make a U-turn on Morena Boulevard and was struck by another 
car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Barrymore of the 1500 block of Coast Walk died about 10 p.m. Monday at 
Scripps Memorial Hospital-La Jolla, the county medical examiner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
His wife, June, 60, was taken to Scripps and released with minor injuries, 
hospital spokeswoman Dilene Pulsipher said. 
</P>
<P>
Detective Richard Riley said Barrymore was driving south on Morena, just south 
of Balboa Avenue, when he tried to turn and collided with a vehicle driven by 
Michael Linville, 19. Linville was not injured; his passenger, Joe McGrath, 19, 
received minor injuries and was taken to Mission Bay Hospital, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Riley said no charges will be pressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
