<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Digital Equipment Corp.: The Maynard, Mass.-based computer maker reported a 
loss of $256.7 million in its fourth quarter, contrasted with a profit of 
$313.2 million in the year-ago period. 
</P>
<P>
The loss came on operating revenue of $3.4 billion, down 4%. For the fiscal 
year ended June 30, after pretax charges of $550 million, net income totaled 
$74.4 million, contrasted with $1.1 billion in the 1989 fiscal year. Total 
operating revenue was up 2% to $12.9 billion. The company said its first 
quarterly loss was mainly attributable to the $400-million cost of its 
restructuring program. About 3,000 employees have left the firm under a 
voluntary severance program implemented as part of that restructuring. The 
company also cited "the continuing economic slowdown" that is affecting U.S. 
and other markets. 
</P>
