WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
SUMMER CHILD CARE OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Children can still enroll in a summer child-care program offered by the Culver 
City Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
The program, which runs until Sept. 10 at the district's four elementary 
schools, offers arts and crafts, music, swimming, games, field trips and other 
activities for kindergarteners through fifth-graders. It operates on weekdays 
from 7:30 a.m. to 6 p.m. and costs $75 a week. Children need not be Culver City 
residents to participate. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call (213) 559-3631. 
</P>
