<P>
BUILDING ORDINANCE OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has temporarily prohibited second-story additions to 
single-family homes while the Planning Department finishes a study on such 
additions. 
</P>
<P>
The urgency ordinance prohibiting additions was approved unanimously Tuesday 
night. Ed Cox, director of community development, said the department is not 
considering prohibiting second-story additions, but rather wants to find better 
ways of building them so they do not harm adjacent properties. 
</P>
<P>
Cox said a report is tentatively scheduled to be presented to the Planning 
Commission Aug. 20. It could then come back to the council for consideration by 
Sept. 25. 
</P>
