<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DUARTE; 
</P>
<P>
FEE FOR PROCESSING PETITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Processing initiative petitions will cost $50 under a resolution adopted by the 
City Council to discourage frivolous petitions. 
</P>
<P>
The resolution, approved Tuesday night, says the fee will be refunded if the 
city clerk certifies within a year that the petition has been filed. 
</P>
<P>
Council members John Hitt and James Kirchner, who voted against the measure, 
said the fee would infringe on the democratic process by putting a heavier 
burden on the poor. 
</P>
<P>
The majority of the council, however, said a fee would deter those who, for 
example, process several petitions and file none, causing city staff wasted 
time and effort. 
</P>
