<P>
GOVERNMENT TROOPS CAPTURE 2 TOWNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Government troops have captured two towns just south of rebel-held Jaffna 
Peninsula, opening a major road into the stronghold of Tamil militants, 
military officials said. 
</P>
<P>
At least 96 of the separatist rebels and 13 soldiers were killed in the 
three-day operation, which gave the government control over Paranthan and 
Kilinochchi. Kilinochchi is linked by highway to the town of Jaffna, where the 
rebel Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam is headquartered. Tamil militants have 
been fighting for an independent homeland since 1983. 
</P>
