<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAVY PLANE CRASHES IN S. CHINA SEA, 2 MISSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.S. Navy attack bomber crashed in the South China Sea on a routine night 
mission, a spokesman for the 7th Fleet said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The pilot and navigator were reported missing. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Lee Saunders said the Grumman A-6E Intruder crashed almost 400 miles 
southwest of Subic Bay Naval Base. 
</P>
<P>
Howard Thomas, a spokesman for the Whidbey Island Naval Air Station in 
Washington state, where the plane was based, identified the missing pilot as 
Lt. Cmdr. Jeffrey Mines, 35, of North Bend, Neb., and the navigator as Lt. 
Cmdr. Arthur Braun, 37, of Georgetown, Tex. 
</P>
