<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORPORATE SPONSORS LINE UP FOR FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With the start of the 1991 U.S. Olympic Festival in Los Angeles less than a 
year away, organizers are still formulating plans and raising money. Wednesday, 
the financial picture brightened considerably with the announcement of five 
additional corporate sponsors. 
</P>
<P>
Elizabeth Primrose-Smith, president of the '91 festival, said corporate 
sponsors would be expected to account for $8 million to $9 million of the 
festival's $13-million budget. 
</P>
<P>
Ticket sales are projected to make up the $4-million remainder. 
</P>
<P>
The Olympic Festival is a multisport competition sponsored by the U.S. Olympic 
Committee and held in every non-Olympic year. The L.A. dates are next July 
12-21 at sites throughout the Southland. 
</P>
<P>
Primrose-Smith said tickets would be available in mid-February. She said the 
festival would need more than 9,000 volunteers, plus another 9,000 for the 
event's torch run. JULIE CART 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
