<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALKER LIKELY TO MISS SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CURT HOLBREICH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wide receiver Wayne Walker will undergo arthroscopic surgery today to repair 
ligament damage in his right knee and likely will be out for the season, Coach 
Dan Henning said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Walker injured the knee in practice Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The loss is significant for the Chargers, who were counting on Walker to be 
among their top three receivers. 
</P>
<P>
"He is a guy that has outstanding speed and quickness, plus he has been a deep 
threat for us," Henning said. 
</P>
<P>
Walker made the team last season as a free agent from Texas Tech after similar 
surgery on his left knee as a senior. He started four games, catching 24 passes 
for 395 yards and a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Henning also said offensive guard Mike Simmonds, a Plan B acquisition from 
Tampa Bay, will undergo arthroscopic knee examination today because of an 
ongoing problem. CURT HOLBREICH 
</P>
</TEXT>
