<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLINTSTONES, JETSONS TO VIE WITH MICKEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wilma! It's time to hit the malls. 
</P>
<P>
Hanna-Barbera Productions, the storied animation house that gave the world the 
Flintstones and the Jetsons, said Wednesday that it will open a store at the 
Westside Pavilion in West Los Angeles Aug. 1. 
</P>
<P>
Another shop is scheduled to open at the Del Amo Fashion Center in Torrance on 
Sept. 1. 
</P>
<P>
The stores will carry clothing, stuffed dolls, toys, games, jewelry and 
collectibles. Hanna-Barbera's first retail outlet began business last month at 
the new Universal Studios Florida tour in Orlando. 
</P>
<P>
Sharp-eyed shoppers will notice that the firm isn't the first show-biz legend 
to go into retailing. It's following the path of Walt Disney Co., which sells 
the likes of Minnie and Mickey at its 50 mall stores. 
</P>
</TEXT>
