<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carter Sentenced: Donald Carter, the former head of a Wall Street company that 
organizes stockholder elections, was sentenced to a prison term of up to four 
years for grand larceny and state income tax evasion. 
</P>
<P>
He was also fined $50,000 and ordered to pay $1 million in restitution to 
clients of his former firm. He will be eligible for parole after serving 16 
months. Carter, who headed Carter Organization Inc., pleaded guilty in March to 
grand larceny charges for stealing $1 million from clients. 
</P>
