<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACTEL, CELLULAR AGREE TO MERGER OF SOME INTERESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pacific Telesis Group and Cellular Communications Inc. said Wednesday that they 
would merge their cellular telephone interests in Ohio and Michigan in a move 
that ultimately will further consolidate the growing industry. 
</P>
<P>
The deal calls for San Francisco-based PacTel to invest at least $87 million 
for an immediate 5% stake in Cellular Communications. Within the next six 
years, PacTel could take over Cellular Communications entirely for another $600 
million or more. 
</P>
<P>
The merger is the latest in a series of recent moves by telecommunications 
companies to strengthen their cellular operations throughout the world. They 
are seeking to take advantage of huge projected growth in radio wave telephone 
services fueled by new technology, improved transmission devices and declining 
equipment prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
