<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NEIGHBORHOOD EATERY: MUFFINS, GOOD COFFEE -- THEY MAKE RISING EARLY WORTH 
IT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA LUTHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The specially blended yogurt at Chelsea's Choice keeps the customers coming 
during the day, especially in the summer. But early mornings, the place belongs 
strictly to the muffin crowd. 
</P>
<P>
Most of those who stop by come for takeout on the way to work. When you've got 
a few minutes to spare, though, Chelsea's is a cheerful place to sit awhile 
with a good cup of coffee and a newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
And, of course, a tasty muffin. There are raspberry and blueberry bran, banana 
walnut, banana oatmeal, oat bran, chocolate chip, carrot nut bran, but the best 
is carrot -- moist, not-too-sweet, with lots of walnuts and perfect spicing. 
</P>
<P>
You also can find novel varieties. On a recent morning, for instance, there 
were "turtles" (made with pecans, caramel and chocolate) and hot fudge muffins 
(with the real stuff, as well as chocolate chips and sour cream). If that's not 
enough, there's a sweet streusel version of some sort each day; blueberry, 
apple and cinnamon are among the favorites. 
</P>
<P>
Chelsea's is worth getting up early for. No day that starts there can be all 
bad. 
</P>
<P>
 Chelsea's Choice, 777 S. Main St. 125, Santa Ana. Open Mondays through Fridays 
6:15 a.m. to 7 p.m., Saturdays from 7:15 a.m. to 5 p.m. (714) 972-9171. 3025 E. 
Coast Highway, Corona del Mar. Open daily 6:30 a.m. to 9 p.m., Sundays from 7 
a.m.. (714) 675-7870. 
</P>
<P>
CLAUDIA LUTHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, The muffin crowd gathers. AURELIO JOSE BARRERA / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
