<TEXT>
<P>
A South African Airways Boeing 747 bound for West Germany turned back to 
Johannesburg with an engine trailing flames, the airline said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
An engine duct ruptured just after the plane, carrying 80 passengers, took off 
for Frankfurt late Tuesday. No one was hurt. 
