ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE TO ATTEND 'VERBAL JUDO' CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city will spend $6,500 next month on a "verbal judo" course designed to 
train its police officers to defuse potentially dangerous conflicts by using 
body language and the spoken word. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday night unanimously approved the allocation from 
narcotic seizure funds. The course has been acclaimed by many Southern 
California law enforcement agencies as effective in reducing complaints against 
departments, Chief James Cook said. 
</P>
<P>
Around 100 officers and dispatchers will attend the program, tentatively set 
for mid-August. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
