<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL APPROVES $500-MILLION PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The latest and largest addition to the Anaheim Stadium business area, Stadium 
Business Park, will bring four high-rise office towers, a 400-room hotel, a 
health club, an eight-story parking garage and retail store space to the 
growing commercial area in the next few years. 
</P>
<P>
Construction of the nearly $500-million project, approved by the City Council 
on Tuesday, is scheduled to begin in about three years, but may start earlier 
with the development of the Anaheim Arena nearby. 
</P>
<P>
The business park, which will include two 20- and two 16-story buildings, will 
be located across the street from the main entrance of Anaheim Stadium on the 
southwest corner of State College Boulevard and Pacifico Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Plans for the project, to be developed and owned by the Los Angeles-based 
Gardner Group, have been two years in the making. 
</P>
<P>
As yet there are no definite agreements with possible tenants, said Steven 
Dietrich, a consultant for the project. LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</TEXT>
