<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN, 92, IS STRICKEN AS SHE TESTIFIES IN SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 92-year-old woman was reported in critical condition Wednesday evening after 
suffering a cerebral hemorrhage while testifying in a civil trial here. 
</P>
<P>
A witness said that Lila Coke had been on the stand in Superior Court for about 
20 minutes when she developed difficulty breathing and became dizzy. 
</P>
<P>
Suddenly, she seemed to freeze, and her lawyer helped her down from the witness 
stand and laid her on the floor. 
</P>
<P>
Jurors were quickly ushered into a back room and paramedics took Coke to 
Western Medical Center-Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
Judge Richard J. Beacom declared a mistrial but retained jurisdiction so that 
new jurors can be picked and the trial can begin again quickly when Coke 
recovers. 
</P>
<P>
In a lawsuit, Coke seeks damages for injuries she suffered several years ago 
when she tripped on a garden hose at Leisure World in Seal Beach, where she 
lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
