<HEADLINE>
<P>
AFTER A SUCCESSFUL TRIP, DUKES ARE HOME TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After five matches on a trip through the East, the Newport Beach Dukes will 
play host to the Sacramento Capitals at 7:30 tonight at the John Wayne Tennis 
Club. 
</P>
<P>
In Team Tennis' West Division, the Capitals (6-2) are half a match ahead of the 
Dukes (5-2) and half a match behind the first-place Los Angeles Strings. The 
Dukes won four of their five road matches. 
</P>
<P>
The Dukes' Amy Frazier, who has a 41-27 record, is the top-ranked women's 
singles player in Team Tennis after seven matches. 
</P>
