<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
EAST GERMANY SEIZES EX-OFFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EAST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former East German Communist security chief Erich Mielke was arrested today on 
suspicion of sheltering fugitive West German guerrillas and planning internment 
camps for dissidents, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The state press agency ADN said an arrest warrant was issued after Mielke, 82, 
was determined fit to be jailed pending completion of inquiries leading to 
possible charges and a trial. 
</P>
<P>
Mielke, once top aide of former East German Stalinist leader Erich Honecker, 
was previously jailed after coming under investigation in December for 
suspected corruption, embezzlement and misrule. But he was freed later because 
of what officials said was poor health. 
</P>
<P>
East Germany last month arrested eight fugitive Red Army Faction guerrilla 
suspects who officials said had lived in the country under false names for 
years, protected by Mielke's State Security Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
