<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities are trying to determine what killed a person whose body was found 
in a casket in a room equipped with an iron cage and sexual bondage 
paraphernalia, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities could not determine immediately whether the decomposed body is that 
of a male or a female, said Harris County Medical Examiner J. L. Ebdon. 
</P>
<P>
The body was found Wednesday wrapped in heavy plastic and bound at the feet 
with duct tape. 
</P>
<P>
"It is very badly decomposed but because of the wrapping, we cannot tell how 
long it has been there," Ebdon said. 
</P>
<P>
Police were called by a friend of the owner to the townhouse where the body was 
found. The man found the casket while looking for tools in an upstairs room and 
opened the casket slightly after smelling a foul odor, Mayer said. 
</P>
<P>
Neighbors told police the home owner is hospitalized recovering from brain 
surgery. 
