<P>
CUBA CALLS DEFECTOR A TRAITOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAVANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cuba Wednesday described jazz trumpeter Arturo Sandoval, who has defected to 
the United States, as a traitor who abandoned his country like a rat leaving a 
ship in danger. 
</P>
<P>
Sandoval decided to defect during a recent tour of Europe and has since 
traveled to the United States, the Cuban news agency Prensa Latina said in a 
rare official Cuban confirmation of a defection. 
</P>
<P>
Prensa Latina quoted a statement from the state-run Cuban Institute of Music as 
saying that the trumpeter had "betrayed his country." 
</P>
<P>
"In times of danger, rats abandon the ship to drown themselves in an infinite 
sea of dishonor and shame," the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
